      <h2>Emergency Plumber Liverpool. Common Questions</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Liverpool homeowners ask most.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">MINIMUM CHARGE</span>&nbsp; Is there a minimum charge?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We charge a minimum of 1 hour on all call-outs. Weekdays 9am to 5pm that is £80. Weekends 9am to 1pm that is £120. Out of hours that is £150. After the first hour we charge in 30 minute increments. Parts are charged at cost. A written quote is provided before any work begins beyond the initial diagnosis.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does an emergency plumber cost in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Fixed hourly rates with a 1 hour minimum: weekdays 9am to 5pm £80, weekends 9am to 1pm £120, out of hours nights and bank holidays £150. After the first hour we charge in 30 minute increments. Parts at cost. Most jobs cost between £80 and £350. Written quote before work begins.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All our engineers are Gas Safe registered. It is illegal to work on gas appliances without this qualification. Verify our registration at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We provide gas safety certificates for all gas work carried out.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">ENGINEERS</span>&nbsp; Do you use sub-contractors?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>No. Every engineer we send to your Liverpool property is our own directly employed staff. We never use sub-contractors or agency workers. You get the same trained, vetted, insured professional every time.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">RESPONSE</span>&nbsp; How quickly can you reach me in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>We guarantee a 30 minute response across Liverpool L1 to L40. Our average arrival time is 28 minutes. City centre, Anfield and Wavertree typically under 20 minutes. Outlying areas like Formby, Kirkby and Maghull around 35 minutes.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">POSTCODES</span>&nbsp; What postcodes do you cover in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>We cover all Liverpool postcodes from L1 to L40 including the city centre, Anfield, Aigburth, Wavertree, West Derby, Woolton, Old Swan, Childwall, Allerton, Garston, Bootle, Crosby, Maghull, Kirkby, Huyton, Norris Green, Fazakerley, Aintree, Formby and Southport.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COMMERCIAL</span>&nbsp; Do you cover commercial properties in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We cover commercial emergencies 24/7 across Liverpool including shops, restaurants, offices, hotels and warehouses. Same fixed rates as residential. No commercial premium. We can invoice on 30-day payment terms for established businesses.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GUARANTEE</span>&nbsp; Do you guarantee your work?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All our work carries a full 12-month workmanship guarantee. If anything we fix fails within 12 months due to our work we come back and sort it at no charge. No argument, no quibble.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">FROZEN PIPES</span>&nbsp; What should I do if my pipes are frozen in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Do not try to thaw frozen pipes with a naked flame. Turn off the water at the stopcock immediately. Call us immediately. A frozen pipe costs far less to fix than a burst one. Liverpool's Victorian terraces are particularly vulnerable due to external and loft pipes that were never insulated to modern standards.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">INSURANCE</span>&nbsp; Can you help with water damage insurance claims?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We provide full documentation for insurance claims including an itemised invoice, photos of the damage and repair, a written report explaining the cause, and gas safety certificates where applicable. We can also correspond directly with your insurer if required.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">LANDLORDS</span>&nbsp; Do you work with Liverpool landlords and letting agents?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We work with individual landlords and letting agents across Liverpool, Wirral, Warrington and St Helens. We provide annual gas safety certificates (CP12) from £80, handle tenant emergency call-outs and offer monthly cover plans for portfolio landlords. See <a href="https://www.nrla.org.uk/resources/gas-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NRLA landlord gas safety guidance</a> for your legal obligations.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">3AM</span>&nbsp; Do you really answer calls at 3am?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. A real person answers 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. No voicemail, no automated system and no call centre. We answer within 3 rings. Christmas Day, Bank Holidays, 3am Sunday mornings. Call us right now to test it.</p></div></details>
      <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">NO HOT WATER</span>&nbsp; What should I do if I have no hot water in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Check your boiler pressure gauge first. It should read between 1 and 1.5 bar. Below 0.5 bar, repressurise using the filling loop. Note any error codes on the boiler display before calling us. If neither resolves the issue, call us on 07399 676656. We attend no hot water emergencies 24/7 across Liverpool.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">BLOCKED DRAIN</span>&nbsp; What should I do if my toilet is blocked or overflowing?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Stop flushing immediately. Continued flushing will overflow sewage onto the floor. Turn off the water supply to the toilet at the isolation valve on the pipe behind it if possible. Call us on 07399 676656. Do not use chemical drain cleaners as these are rarely effective on full blockages and can damage older Liverpool pipework.</p></div></details>
